notes: Shahid Afridi's century in 37 balls (ODI record)
11 sixes in Shahid Afridi's innings ties ODI record (set by S.T.Jayasuriya)
Saeed Anwar's 9th ODI century. Along with Rameez Raja, Lara and Tendulkar, maximum for a currently active batsman.
Sri Lanka required 290 to make the final on net run rate
Pakistan and South Africa enter the finals.
Man of the match adjudicator: RJ Shastri

milestones.description: Shahid Afridi has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (90) in an innings in ODIs for PAK, going past Ijaz Ahmed's 86
Shahid Afridi has broken the record for most sixes in an innings (11) in ODIs for PAK, going past Saeed Anwar's 6
de Silva and Dharmasena's 110-run partnership is SL's highest for the 7th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 90 between Ranatunga and Uvais Karnain
